job_description:
Location: Rotterdam, The Netherlands

Department: Marketing

Type of employment: full-time


HMS’ business unit Anybus is looking for a technical copywriter to join the marketing team in Rotterdam, The Netherlands.

We are looking for a person who knows the challenges of marketing a technical or industrial product. Whether you are selling hardware, software or a service, you are confident to communicate features and benefits without boring the target audience or getting caught up in technical details.

You do not have to be an expert on the type of products we develop, but you do need to feel confident about tackling technical topics. You should be comfortable doing research and have the ability to think critically. You should be able to provide background information, to shorten the learning curve. The more complex your topic, the greater your ability to provide input.

In this role you will need to understand how our solutions work, who it is for and how it solves the challenges faced.

You will have an important role in a small and efficient marketing team that produces content marketing, product launches, digital marketing campaigns, web content, sales presentations, and trainings.

HMS Networks has been acknowledged as a great place to work, due to our friendly and welcoming environment. The Anybus marketing team is located at HMS' head office in Halmstad, where we are close to developers, engineers and technical professionals. In addition, we work closely with people from HMS own sales and support offices located in 16 different countries around the world.

 Responsibilities:

Research and communicate topics in clear, concise ways to a non-technical audience;
Produce text for large projects such as product brochures, press releases, data sheets, customer success stories/case studies, whitepapers etc.;
Knowledge of and ability to produce text for small marketing activities such as newsletter posts, blog posts, texts for web, and social media;
Work collaboratively within a cross-functional team environment with designers, engineers, and product managers;
Translate complex strategic approaches into easily accessible creative concepts;
Background in the industrial automation industry and strong understanding of marketing automation tools is a plus;
Excellent English writing skills.
